description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The successful applicant will be dynamic, highly motivated individuals, with excellent interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to work autonomously and as a member of the special school nursing team. As a Staff Nurse you will be working as part of pro-active skill mix team who are committed to delivering high quality services to children, young people and their families.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities will include caring for children with urinary catheters, stoma and PEG feeds and with an awareness of tracheostomy care within the school and community settings. Developing specialist individual care plans to meet the child/young person’s needs.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Undertake holistic assessments of children, young people and families in planning and delivering the Healthy Child Programme, including health screening and immunisations, plus a requirement to safeguard and support the health needs of any vulnerable children/young people within the caseload across the city.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Plan and manage complex activities and programmes that require constant &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;adjustment to meet the changing needs of children / young people.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Using additional equipment the child / young person may require on a daily basis, or in an emergency. Have an awareness of the support required for children/young people with tracheostomy&#39;s. Care of children/young people requiring urinary catheters, and peg feeds in the school and community settings in line with a competency framework&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Applicants must demonstrate an understanding of current trends and developments in school health practice and have a commitment to reducing health inequalities&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful applicants will benefit from a full induction and mentorship programme. Regular clinical and safeguarding supervision will also be provided as will access to relevant internal and external training/development opportunities&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shortlisting is planned for: 10th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are planned for: 18th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rhiannon Evans- School Health Clinical Team Leader&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;nicola.tucker@merseycare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
